HEADWORD: Dipsas
<hw>Dip"sas</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., fr. Gr. <?/, fr.
<?/ thirst.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A serpent whose bite was fabled to
produce intense thirst.</def> <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A genus of harmless colubrine
snakes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dipsetic</ent>⟦br⟧
